fter [[:en:July 19|July 19]] (Natsugoshi Festival) |prefecture = {{ill|Tenjin|qid=Q603281}} |coordinates = {{Coord|33.58761111111111|N|130.3996111111111|E|region:JP_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} |deity = {{ill|Magatsuhinokami|qid=Q11591203}}; {{ill|Naobinokami|qid=Q11581794}} }} {{osm box|n|384542332}}
'''Kego Shrine''' (けごじんじゃ) is a [[:en:Fukuoka Prefecture|Fukuoka Prefecture]] [[:en:Fukuoka|Fukuoka City]] {{ill|Fukuoka City Chuo Ward|de|Fukuoka City Chuo Ward|ja|福岡市中央区 (福岡市)|lt=Chuo Ward|lt_ja=中央区|lt_de=Fukuoka City Chuo Ward|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fukuoka City Chuo Ward|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} located at Tenjin 2-2-20, and is a [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shrine]]. Its former shrine Rank was {{ill|Prefectural Shrine|de|Präfektur-Schrein|ja|県社|lt=Ken-sha|1=Modern_system_of_ranked_Shinto_shrines#Metropolitan_and_Prefectural_Shrines|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Prefectural Shrine|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 近代社格制度}}.
==Enshrined Deities== Kego Ōkami (the three deities): * {{ill|Yasomagatsuhinokami|de|Yasomagatsuhinokami|ja|禍津日神|lt=Yasomagatsuhinokami|lt_ja=八十禍津日神|lt_de=Yasomagatsuhinokami|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yasomagatsuhinokami|qq=}} (yasomagatsuhinokami) * {{ill|Kannaobi no Kami|de|Kannaobi no Kami|ja|直毘神|lt=Kannaobi no Kami|lt_ja=神直毘神|lt_de=Kannaobi no Kami|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kannaobi no Kami|qq=}} (kannaobi no kami) * {{ill|Kannaobi no Kami|de|Kannaobi no Kami|ja|直毘神|lt=Great Kannaobi no Kami|lt_ja=大直毘神|lt_de=Great Kannaobi no Kami|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kannaobi no Kami|qq=}} (great kannaobi no kami)
==History== According to shrine legend, during the {{ill|Conquest of the Three Han|de|Eroberung der Drei Han|ja|三韓征伐|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Conquest of the Three Han|qq=}}, Empress Jingū’s fleet was protected and led to victory by Kego Ōkami, who was then enshrined at Fukasaki (around the area of the main bailey of [[:en:Fukuoka Castle|Fukuoka Castle]]), marking the beginning of the shrine. In the 6th year of the [[:en:Keichō|Keichō era]] ([[:en:1601|1601]]), during the construction of Fukuoka Castle, the shrine was moved to Shimokego Village (in the area around present-day [[:en:Fukuoka|Fukuoka City]], {{ill|Fukuoka City Chuo Ward|de|Fukuoka City Chuo Ward|ja|福岡市中央区 (福岡市)|lt=Chuo Ward|lt_ja=中央区|lt_de=Fukuoka City Chuo Ward|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fukuoka City Chuo Ward|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, [[:en:Tenjin (kami)|Tenjin]])). In the 13th year of the [[:en:Keichō|Keichō era]] ([[:en:1608|1608]]), [[:en:Kuroda Nagamasa|Kuroda Nagamasa]], the lord of Fukuoka Castle, had a shrine building erected at its current location. In the 5th year of the [[:en:Taishō era|Taishō era]] ([[:en:1916|1916]]), it was Ranked as a Prefectural Shrine.
The shrine’s name and the surrounding area “Kego” derive from the former government office “Kegosho” that was once located in the [[:en:Kōrokan|Kōrokukan]].
==Facilities== [[File:Haiden of Kego Shrine 2.jpg|thumb|240px|[[:en:Haiden (Shinto)|Haiden]]]] [[File:Shimmon Gate of Kego Shrine.JPG|thumb|240px|{{ill|Shinmon Gate|de|Shinmon Gate|ja|神門|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinmon Gate|qq=}}]] * Haiden (Worship Hall) * Honden (Main Hall) * Great Torii * Shinmon Gate * Harinoki Monument * Ima Masu Inari Shrine * Shintoku Hall (rental venue)
{{ill|Kego Park|de|Kego Park|ja|警固公園|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kego Park|qq=}} borders the northern side of the shrine.
==Access== * [[:en:Nishi-Nippon Railroad|Nishi-Nippon Railroad]] [[:en:Nishitetsu Tenjin Ōmuta Line|Tenjin Omuta Line]] [[:en:Nishitetsu Fukuoka (Tenjin) Station|Nishitetsu Fukuoka (Tenjin) Station]] (South Exit) 1-minute walk * {{ill|Fukuoka City Subway|de|Fukuoka City Subway|ja|福岡市交通局|lt=Fukuoka City Subway|lt_ja=福岡市地下鉄|lt_de=Fukuoka City Subway|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fukuoka City Subway|qq=|comment=enwiki is a redirect}} [[:en:Kūkō Line (Fukuoka City Subway)|Airport Line]] [[:en:Tenjin Station|Tenjin Station]] 7-minute walk * Fukuoka City Subway [[:en:Nanakuma Line|Nanakuma Line]] [[:en:Tenjin-Minami Station|Tenjin-Minami Station]] 4-minute walk * {{ill|Nishitetsu Bus|de|Nishitetsu Bus|ja|西鉄バス|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nishitetsu Bus|qq=}} “Tenjin Kego Shrine – [[:en:Mitsukoshi|Mitsukoshi]] Front” 1-minute walk
==Photographs== <Gallery> File:Stone monument at Kego-jinja.JPG File:Stone animal monument at Kego-jinja.jpg </Gallery>
==External Links== {{Commonscat|Kego-jinja}}
*[http://www.kegojinja.or.jp/ Kego Shrine] (official website) {{Shinto Side}} {{shinto-stub}}
